# WhatsApp Platform

Canonical docs: `docs/whatsapp-platform/CURRENT-SCOPE.md`, `ARCHITECTURE.md`, `DOCUMENTATION-MAP.md`.  
Safe-change skill: `.cursor/skills/whatsapp-platform-safe-change.md`.  
UI: `.cursor/rules/whatsapp-platform-design.mdc`.

## Ownership (where work belongs)

| Path | Responsibility | Status |
|------|----------------|--------|
| `apps/whatsapp-platform` | Canonical runtime: UI, handlers, Prisma, auth composition, webhook Meta, Stripe, inbox | **active** |
| `packages/whatsapp-core` | Pure rules, contracts, reusable WhatsApp domain logic | **shared** |
| `packages/whatsapp-routes` | Cutover/landing/route constants for portal & shared surfaces | **shared** |
| `packages/billing-core` | Shared plans, quotas, billing, entitlement rules | **shared** |
| `packages/ai-core` | Shared AI contracts / mechanisms | **shared** |
| `packages/analytics-core` | Shared metrics / events | **shared** |
| `src/` (portal) | Public acquisition, commercial pages, demo mock, internal CRM | **active** (non-ops) |
| `apps/whatsapp-webhook-api` | Legacy Express surface — keep compatible; **no new product features** | **legacy-compatible** |

Status: `active` | `shared` | `legacy-compatible` | `migration-source` | `deprecated` | `historical`.

Prefer packages for reusable pure logic; compose in the app. Do not implement new ops features in the portal or `whatsapp-webhook-api`.

## Boundaries (forbidden)

- `packages/whatsapp-core` — no Next.js, Prisma Client, Stripe SDK, or Meta SDK.
- `packages/whatsapp-routes` — do not redefine domain rules that belong in core/app.
- `apps/whatsapp-platform` — do not duplicate contracts already in packages; extend packages instead.
- Portal `src/` — no WhatsApp app Prisma; no imports from `apps/whatsapp-platform` (CI guard).
- UI — does not authoritatively resolve tenant, entitlement, or authorization.
- Client — must not choose authoritative `tenantId`, `phoneNumberId`, or plan limits.

## Non-negotiables

- **Deploy:** webhook URL and OAuth on the **app** host (`NEXT_PUBLIC_WHATSAPP_APP_URL`) — `apps/whatsapp-platform/docs/DEPLOY_APP_SUBDOMAIN.md`.
- **Tenant:** resolve via `phone_number_id` / existing models; never process inbound without a valid tenant.
- **Webhook Meta:** GET verify + POST; signature; retries; idempotency — `docs/architecture/WHATSAPP-WEBHOOK-HARDENING.md`.
- **Stripe / quotas:** align with `packages/billing-core` and app billing docs.
- **Audit:** keep or extend audit trails on sensitive inbox/ops changes.
- **Before first edit:** produce the impact map required by the safe-change skill (domain, owners, tenant, auth, tests, out-of-scope).

## Quality gates (minimum)

| Change | Gates |
|--------|--------|
| Pure domain | `test:node` |
| Component/UI | `test:ui`, lint, design system |
| Inbox | `test:node`, `test:ui`, `test:e2e:inbox` |
| Critical visual | E2E + a11y |
| Webhook Meta | `test:node`, `smoke`, `ops:check-channel` |
| Billing | `test:node`, integration/idempotency review |
| Prisma | generate, migration validation, tenant isolation tests |
| Design system | visual lint + `test:a11y:product-ui` |

Small diffs; inspect existing handlers/services before new paths.
